    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.4.31"/>
                <note type="curatorial">31</note>
                <note type="curatorial">
                    Fink Collection 
                    711
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    <fw type="authorial">
                        <figure/> H.B. PAYNE, PRESIDENT 
                        E.M. SLATER, VICE PRESIDENT 
                        WEI 
                    </fw>

                    <dateline>
                        [May 1, 1923] ?
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Enid: -</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Your good letter reached me at Spencer, and I was so glad to get it. I read it just as soon as I got my hands on it, you can be sure. Grandma says you are all good children, and that doesn't surprise me, tho' I was glad to hear it. I'll be at home on the 13th or 14th, and I'll be the gladdest person!</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Lots of love,</salute>
                    <signed>Daddy</signed>
                </closer> 
                <postscript><p>Tell Alice her Daddy loves her.</p></postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
